                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "EPJ Web of Conferences 206, 03004 (2019) https://doi.org/10.1051/epjconf/201920603004",
            "section": "Table 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 40,
            "section_rank": 12,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 4,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "EPJ",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "As for the two-jet case, expansion of the \u03c4-model expression does not lead to significant improvement in the fits. ",
            "section": "Table 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 41,
            "section_rank": 14
        },
        {
            "text": "This validates the use of an asymmetric L\u00e9vy distribution for the longitudinal proper time.",
            "section": "Table 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 41,
            "section_rank": 14
        },
        {
            "text": "However, significant improvement of the fit is obtained by letting R a be a free parameter. ",
            "section": "Table 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 42,
            "section_rank": 14
        },
        {
            "text": "i.e., by lessening the connection of the simplified \u03c4-model between the BEC peak and the antisymmetric dip. ",
            "section": "Table 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 42,
            "section_rank": 14
        },
        {
            "text": "Whether letting \u03c4 0 also be a free parameter would also give significant improvement is the subject of ongoing investigation, as is the question whether \u03b1 decreases as the number of jets increases.",
            "section": "Table 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 42,
            "section_rank": 14
        },
        {
            "text": "S. L\u00f6k\u00f6s greatfully acknowledges the support from the ERASMUS project of the EU and thanks W. Metzger for his kind hospitality at the Radboud University Nijmegen, The Netherlands. ",
